# Merge Sort

## Problem

Merge Sort is a Divide and Conquer sorting algorithm that divides the array into two halves, sorts them recursively, and then merges the sorted halves.

---

# Algorithm / Pseudo Code

BEGIN

MERGESORT(A, low, high)

IF low < high

    COMPUTE mid = (low + high) / 2

    CALL MERGESORT(A, low, mid)

    CALL MERGESORT(A, mid+1, high)

    CALL MERGE(A, low, mid, high)

ENDIF

END


MERGE(A, low, mid, high)

CREATE temporary arrays L and R

COPY left half into L
COPY right half into R

INITIALIZE i = 0
INITIALIZE j = 0
INITIALIZE k = low

WHILE i < size of L AND j < size of R

    IF L[i] <= R[j]

        A[k] = L[i]
        i = i + 1

    ELSE

        A[k] = R[j]
        j = j + 1

    ENDIF

    k = k + 1

ENDWHILE

COPY remaining elements of L into A

COPY remaining elements of R into A

END

